BATTERY+ ---- fuse ----- REMOVABLE_SWITCH (external) ---- MAIN_POS_BUS ---+--> ESC1(+)
                                                                          +--> ESC2(+)
                                                                          +--> SOLENOID_POWER(+)  (if solenoid runs on battery)
BATTERY- --------------------------------------------------------------+--> ESC1(-), ESC2(-), SOLENOID(-)
                                                                          (common ground to Rx/Arduino)

ESC1 signal (throttle left) --> RX CH1
ESC2 signal (throttle right) --> RX CH2

If using BEC:
  ESC1 BEC (5V)  --> RX Vcc  (only ONE BEC active; disable others)
  Or UBEC 5V --> RX Vcc

RX CH3 (weapon channel) --> Arduino pulse input (or directly to relay if no Arduino)
Arduino (or Rx) --> Relay/MOSFET gate --> Solenoid negative
Solenoid positive -> MAIN_POS_BUS

POWER LED: small LED + resistor across BATTERY+ and BATTERY- (visible externally)
ARM SWITCH: mechanical switch wired to Arduino arm input (or wired to cut main power physically)
LOCK PIN: mechanical pin (no wiring) used during tech inspection
